law.text:
The cabinet, as it deems necessary and advisable, may:
Consult with agencies of the state, federal, and local government in order to coordinate development programs and plans and to articulate agriculture, industry, and commerce in the light of the needs of particular localities;
Make studies of land utilization so as to determine areas suitable for industrial and commercial development;
Make studies and projections and publish information relating to the economic development of the Commonwealth and make appropriate recommendations to the board and the General Assembly;
Establish and maintain development offices in out-of-state centers of industrial and commercial management;
Place advertising in appropriate media promoting Kentucky's resources and locational advantages for industrial and commercial enterprises.
